<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.5/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-O1HfhcSrdCAKGBTRVqt73w" name=",_8_mWgH3GEd2sJcA0evSBQw" guid="-O1HfhcSrdCAKGBTRVqt73w" authors="Jerome Boyer" changeDate="2008-09-08T14:11:17.033-0300">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    A term may describe business concept as defined by the business. So a term is related to the language of the people&#xD;
    within the company. A term used in one group may differ in its meaning within another group. Term in SBVR is a concept&#xD;
    and can be declined as noun concept or verb concept.Term represents a unit of knowledge with a unique combination of&#xD;
    characteristics. In Object Oriented Analysis we will map to a Class.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Fact is a combination of terms that describes what business people know about their business. Fact may describe the&#xD;
    relationship between terms, like an Insurance Policy is a form of Contract, or it may describe the interactions between&#xD;
    terms (collaboration).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Taking as an example a rule description like:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        &lt;em>Ask for an audit if&amp;nbsp; one of the treatment includes an emergency room treatment or an ambulance transfer&#xD;
        done on a day after the accident&lt;/em>.&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The analysis team can extract the following business terms: audit, treatment, emergency room, ambulance transfer, day&#xD;
    of accident, accident. Discussing with a claim processor we can extract the following facts:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div&#xD;
        style=&quot;MARGIN-TOP: 4.32pt; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: baseline; DIRECTION: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; TEXT-ALIGN: left; language: en-US; mso-line-break-override: restrictions; punctuation-wrap: simple&quot;>&#xD;
            A&amp;nbsp;car accident is declared in a claim&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div&#xD;
        style=&quot;MARGIN-TOP: 4.32pt; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: baseline; DIRECTION: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; TEXT-ALIGN: left; language: en-US; mso-line-break-override: restrictions; punctuation-wrap: simple&quot;>&#xD;
            Claim has a type, and a date of loss&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div&#xD;
        style=&quot;MARGIN-TOP: 4.32pt; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: baseline; DIRECTION: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; TEXT-ALIGN: left; language: en-US; mso-line-break-override: restrictions; punctuation-wrap: simple&quot;>&#xD;
            There&amp;nbsp;may be&amp;nbsp;some injuries,&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div&#xD;
        style=&quot;MARGIN-TOP: 4.32pt; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: baseline; DIRECTION: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; TEXT-ALIGN: left; language: en-US; mso-line-break-override: restrictions; punctuation-wrap: simple&quot;>&#xD;
            Medical treatments are done by medical providers&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div&#xD;
        style=&quot;MARGIN-TOP: 4.32pt; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: baseline; DIRECTION: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; TEXT-ALIGN: left; language: en-US; mso-line-break-override: restrictions; punctuation-wrap: simple&quot;>&#xD;
            The medical provider issues medical bill&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div&#xD;
        style=&quot;MARGIN-TOP: 4.32pt; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: baseline; DIRECTION: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; TEXT-ALIGN: left; language: en-US; mso-line-break-override: restrictions; punctuation-wrap: simple&quot;>&#xD;
            A medical bill includes the description of the medical treatment done on the patient&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p&#xD;
style=&quot;MARGIN-TOP: 4.32pt; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: baseline; DIRECTION: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; TEXT-ALIGN: left; language: en-US; mso-line-break-override: restrictions; punctuation-wrap: simple&quot;>&#xD;
    Insurance wants to verify the treatment done, and limit the payments on what is defined in the policy and the legal&#xD;
    engagements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br&#xD;
style=&quot;MARGIN-TOP: 4.32pt; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: baseline; DIRECTION: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; TEXT-ALIGN: left; language: en-US; mso-line-break-override: restrictions; punctuation-wrap: simple&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;p&#xD;
style=&quot;MARGIN-TOP: 4.32pt; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: baseline; DIRECTION: ltr; unicode-bidi: embed; TEXT-ALIGN: left; language: en-US; mso-line-break-override: restrictions; punctuation-wrap: simple&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span style=&quot;mso-bidi-language: HE&quot;>Later on in the project the facts have to be analyzed to understand how the&#xD;
    software application will support it. It can be through implementing the logic, the GUI layout, structuring&amp;nbsp;the&#xD;
    different&amp;nbsp;data models or just staying in documentation.&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
